cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on lexical ambiguity resolution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses unsupervised clustering techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of probabilistic models and EM-based clustering techniques suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of probabilistic models and clustering techniques could also suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
